# Implementation Plan: CockroachDB Dual Memory Backend Support

Update FastAPI `database.py` and `main.py` using `psycopg2` to implement CockroachDB Dual Memory patterns: Row-Level TTL for active ephemeral incidents and pgvector cosine similarity search (`vector_cosine_ops`) for incident memory.

## User Review Required

> [!NOTE]
> The backend database module will use `psycopg2` and CockroachDB's `EXPIRE AT now() + INTERVAL '24 hours'` Row-Level TTL syntax for active incidents, while utilizing `vector_cosine_ops` similarity queries against `incident_memory`. In-memory fallbacks ensure smooth execution even if a live CockroachDB cluster is offline.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Database & WebSocket API

#### [MODIFY] [database.py](file:///c:/Users/saake/Downloads/sentinel-agent-main/sentinel-agent-main/backend/database.py)

1. **`log_ephemeral_incident(title: str, summary: str, details: str = "") -> dict`**:
   - Executes SQL query inserting into `active_incidents` with CockroachDB Row-Level TTL:
     ```sql
     INSERT INTO active_incidents (title, summary, details)
     VALUES (%s, %s, %s)
     EXPIRE AT now() + INTERVAL '24 hours'
     RETURNING id;
     ```
   - Includes in-memory fallback storage if DB pool is offline.

2. **`search_past_incidents(embedding: list[float], top_k: int = 3) -> list[dict]`**:
   - Queries `incident_memory` table using `vector_cosine_ops` (or cosine distance calculation `<=>`):
     ```sql
     SELECT id, title, summary, 1 - (embedding <=> %s::vector) AS similarity
     FROM incident_memory
     ORDER BY embedding <=> %s::vector
     LIMIT %s;
     ```
   - Returns top 3 matches along with calculated similarity distance.

3. **`_setup_schema()`**:
   - Creates `active_incidents` (with TTL) and `incident_memory` tables with vector extension setup.
   - Seeds default past incidents into `incident_memory`.

#### [MODIFY] [main.py](file:///c:/Users/saake/Downloads/sentinel-agent-main/sentinel-agent-main/backend/main.py)

- Update `/ws/alert` WebSocket endpoint to call `search_past_incidents()` and stream `pastIncidents` (with similarity distances) and `mcpAuditLogs` payloads back to frontend clients so `AgentMemoryPanel` renders them dynamically in real time.

